[`slots.add()`](https://github.com/KMiri-rs/asterinas/blob/237cb36e0cbca9d6901a8a28a939f60f6132890a/ostd/src/mm/frame/meta.rs#L551-L565) requires the return ptr must have the same allocation with `slots`, while `slots` doesn't have no provenance because `slots` is converted from a usize.


```rust
    let slots = paddr_to_vaddr(paddr) as *mut MetaSlot;

    for i in 0..tot_nr_frames {
        // SAFETY: The memory is successfully allocated with `tot_nr_frames`
        // slots so the index must be within the range.
        let slot = unsafe { slots.add(i) };
        // SAFETY: The memory is just allocated so we have exclusive access and
        // it's valid for writing.
        unsafe {
            slot.write(MetaSlot {
                storage: UnsafeCell::new([0; FRAME_METADATA_MAX_SIZE]),
                ref_count: AtomicU64::new(REF_COUNT_UNUSED),
                vtable_ptr: UnsafeCell::new(MaybeUninit::uninit()),
                in_list: AtomicU64::new(0),
            })
        };
    }
```

~~A direct fix is to use integer computation to get the slot element, keeping provenance discarded and allocation separated.~~ Edit: no, this doesn't work; still the error.

Miri code: https://github.com/KMiri-rs/miri/blob/c78c027e96816eac88366d8f9b81a40e89a7f5a3/src/borrow_tracker/stacked_borrows/diagnostics.rs#L544-L557

```rust
fn error_cause(stack: &Stack, prov_extra: ProvenanceExtra) -> &'static str {
    if let ProvenanceExtra::Concrete(tag) = prov_extra {
        if (0..stack.len())
            .map(|i| stack.get(i).unwrap())
            .any(|item| item.tag() == tag && item.perm() != Permission::Disabled)
        {
            ", but that tag only grants SharedReadOnly permission for this location"
        } else {
            ", but that tag does not exist in the borrow stack for this location"
        }
    } else {
        ", but no exposed tags have suitable permission in the borrow stack for this location" // 👈
    }
}
```
